		<w:t>The completion of this project within the estimated effort specified in this document assumes the full commitment and participation of your management and personnel, including the timely completion of the tasks outlined in Customer Responsibilities below, to minimize the occurrence of â€œlost timeâ€. Lost time is defined as hours where an IBM consultant is onsite and available to perform the tasks as agreed upon with you, but unable to perform or complete those tasks due to customer-induced delays, such as delays in completing your responsibilities, delays due to lengthy change management windows, or other similar delays caused by you.  Lost time is billable, and excessive lost time may cause project delays outside of IBMâ€™s control and/or require additional unanticipated effort for IBM to complete the project beyond what has been estimated in this document.</w:t>

</w:p>

		<w:t>A non-production instance (â€œTestâ€) that is a scaled-down replica of the production instance (hardware, software, connectivity, applications), where configurations and changes are first tested and validated for production-readiness, and where minimal change control procedures are in place.  Any change that will eventually be implemented in production will be introduced here first and thoroughly tested prior to any production roll out.  To the degree that this environment is not a scaled-down replica of the production environment, IBM may not be able to validate certain Tivoli configuration requirements prior to production deployment.  This could result in unanticipated deployment issues in the production environment that could require additional time and effort beyond the estimates provided.</w:t>
